Definition.WordDefinition: airspace \air"space`\ n. 1. the atmosphere above a nation and deemed to be under its jurisdiction. [WordNet 1.5]
air space n : the space in the atmosphere immediately above the earth [syn: {airspace}]

airspace n 1: the space in the atmosphere immediately above the earth [syn: {air space}] 2: the atmosphere above a nation that is deemed to be under its jurisdiction; "the plane was refused permission to enter Chinese airspace"
